samples.commui
Class Community

java.lang.Object
  samples.commui.Community
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.nokia.sm.net.SnapEventListener, java.lang.Runnable, AsyncCommandListener, ButtonListListener, EventListener
public class Community
extends java.lang.Object
implements AsyncCommandListener, com.nokia.sm.net.SnapEventListener, ButtonListListener, EventListener, java.lang.Runnable

Main manager class for MazeRacer sample game functionality.

Primary responsiblities include: management of SNAP session and all communication with SNAP servers, including sending events and intercepting results and errors; management of the various screens in the app GUI; and storage and management of all screen-independent user and game data.

handleChallenge

public void handleChallenge(java.lang.String name,
                            java.lang.String gameRoom,
                            int leader)
Handle incoming game challenges from other users.

If "leader" is 1, then this player is initiating the challenge, so a specially formatted Chat message will be sent to the opponent, inviting them to a game.

If leader is "0", then we were challenged, and this method is called in order to accept the challenge.

Both challenger and challenged call "gameStart" to intiate the game.

Parameters:
name - Name of opponent in game challenge
gameRoom - Name of gameroom to join to start game
leader - "1" if we are the challenger, "0" if we are the challenged.

handlePresenceUpdate

public void handlePresenceUpdate(com.nokia.sm.net.ItemList il)
Handles incoming friend Presence update callbacks from SNAP Servers. Analyzes user state such as GCID, in-game flag, availability, and matchmaking mode to decide whether the user is online and available, online and unavailable, or offline.

Parameters:
il - ItemList containing buddy presence information

handleGameStartCancel

protected boolean handleGameStartCancel(com.nokia.sm.net.ItemList cmd)
gameStartCancel commands must be sent out in a parallel thread from the one that sends the gameStart command, since gameStart itself blocks for up to 30 or so seconds (depending on SNAP Server defaults.)

gameStartCancel() is the only SNAP command that may be sent out in parallel to any other SNAP commands [with the exception of the retrieveAllEvents() command, which is typically called behind the scenes by the SNAP EventListener thread inside ServerComm.] If any other SNAP commands are executed in parallel in this fashion, they will result in a "755 CommandInProgress" error.

Parameters:
cmd - ItemList containing command parameters (primarily, the command listener.)

cancelNonCriticalCmds

public void cancelNonCriticalCmds()
Cancels "non-critical" game commands by removing them from the outgoing SNAP command queue. Non-critical commands are player position updates and heartbeat notifications. This method is called when a game state transition message must go out (e.g., if a player has reached the end of the maze) -- typically it's better to let this command supercede all queued up movement commands and get out to the opponent immediately.

processServerError

public void processServerError(int error,
                               java.lang.String msg,
                               int severity)
SnapEventListener callback. All SNAP Mobile server errors are received here, both synchronous and asynchronous errors. This method saves server errors, to be checked for later in the main event loop that submits commands. Some Views handle their own errors (via commandCompleted() implementations), but unhandled errors eventually get displayed in generic error dialogs by Community (in the run() method).

Note: only errors of type SEVERITY_NON_FATAL are handled by individual Views. All other severity levels are handled generically, in this method.

Specified by:
processServerError in interface com.nokia.sm.net.SnapEventListener
Parameters:
error - Error number to process
msg - Error Message
severity - Severity of the Error Message
